cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of RETURNN, a neural toolkit, for applications in translation and speech recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of deep recurrent encoder networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of pretraining schemes and alternative architectures, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of fast CUDA LSTM kernels, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
